  "text": "Yeast has been used as a model host for many eukaryotic viruses [CITATION_1] . The power of yeast genetics has greatly facilitated our understanding of viral replication. In this report, we demonstrated for the first time that a segment of plant negative-strand RNA virus genome expressed from cloned cDNA can be a template for viral RNA polymerase in yeast.",
